/ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methods</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toSource\"><code>Object.prototype.toSource()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>ArrayBuffer()</code></strong> constructor is used to create\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer\"><code>ArrayBuffer</code></a> objects.\n</p><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/arraybuffer-constructor.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ArrayBuffer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>length<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"length\"><code>length</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The size, in bytes, of the array buffer to create.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  A new <code>ArrayBuffer</code> object of the specified size. Its contents are\n  initialized to 0.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/RangeError\"><code>RangeError</code></a> is thrown if the <code>length</code> is larger than\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/MAX_SAFE_INTEGER\"><code>Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER</code></a> (&gt;= 2 ** 53) or negative.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"creating_an_arraybuffer","title":"Creating an ArrayBuffer","isH3":true,"content":"<p>In this example, we create a 8-byte buffer with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Int32Array\"><code>Int32Array</code></a> view referring to the buffer:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> buffer <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ArrayBuffer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">8</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> view   <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Int32Array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>buffer<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://tc39.es/ecma262/multipage/structured-data.html#sec-arraybuffer-constructor","title":"ECMAScript Language Specification"}],"query":"javascript.builtins.ArrayBuffer.ArrayBuffer"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.ArrayBuffer.ArrayBuffer","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer/ArrayBuffer/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"compatibility_notes","title":"Compatibility notes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  Starting with ECMAScript 2015, <code>ArrayBuffer</code> constructors require to be\n  constructed with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/new\"><code>new</code></a> operator. Calling an\n  <code>ArrayBuffer</code> constructor as a function without <code>new</code>, will throw\n  a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/TypeError\"><code>TypeError</code></a> from now on.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> dv <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">ArrayBuffer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// TypeError: calling a builtin ArrayBuffer constructor</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// without new is forbidden</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> dv <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ArrayBuffer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://github.com/zloirock/core-js#ecmascript-typed-arrays\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Polyfill of <code>ArrayBuffer</code> in <code>core-js</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Typed_arrays\">JavaScript typed arrays</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/SharedArrayBuffer\"><code>SharedArrayBuffer</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The ArrayBuffer() constructor is used to create\n  ArrayBuffer objects.","popularity":0.0019,"modified":"2022-03-10T00:12:43.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"ArrayBuffer() コンストラクター","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"ArrayBuffer() 생성자","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/arraybuffer/arraybuffer","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/arraybuffer/arraybuffer/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/59844b30d33301cd40ac27ab81050d36249fb743","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"JavaScript reference"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Standard built-in objects"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer","title":"ArrayBuffer"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer/ArrayBuffer","title":"ArrayBuffer() constructor"}],"pageTitle":"ArrayBuffer() constructor - JavaScript | MDN","noIndexing":false}}